Class RailYard

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.classes.RailYard

  • public class RailYard
extends java.lang.Object
    CS252 Object-Oriented Programming
    RailYard Class. Has a stack Field for every TrainCard color. This method also takes care of collecting from the hand and sending to the track.
    Author:
    George Kokiadis csd3962@csd.uoc.gr

      • placeInRailYard

        public void placeInRailYard(TrainCard[] cards,
                            Player opponent)
                     throws InvalidColourException,
                            NoCardsSelectedException
        Place selected cards in railyard.
        Pre Conditions : cards[] , opponent are valid objects. Also, opponent is the enemy player, and cards[] is not empty. Also, check for the case of train robbing.
        Post Conditions : Cards are transfered from the Hand to RailYard.
        Parameters:
        cards - Cards to transfer
        opponent - Inactive Player
        Throws:
        InvalidColourException - Thrown when invalid colours are picked
        NoCardsSelectedException - Thrown when the user has not picked any cards
